<TITLE> MRP applications available in Rajshahi </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Rajshahi, Apr 25 (bdnews24.com)Distribution of applications for machine readable passports began in Rajshahi on Sunday. The project was launched in the Dhaka office on Apr 1. Parvin Banu, director of the passport and immigration directorate, had told bdnews24.com that nine other regional passport offices would start receiving applications between Apr 18 and Apr 20. The facility will gradually be made available to all the 24 regional passport offices. The applicants will be given new passports from May. Brig Gen Refayet Ullah, project director for MRPs and MRVs (Machine Readable Visas), inaugurated the programme at Rajshahi regional passport office. A discussion on the benefits and security issues was also organised. Refayet Ullah said that once the MRPs were available, applicants would be saved from a lot of hassle. Moreover, it will also stop people from acquiring more than one passport, he added. Fee for the general passports is Tk 3,000 and Tk 6,000 urgent ones. There are currently about 1.2 crore passport holders in the country. bdne
